# GPIB MCP — VS Code install (#89)

VS Code (GitHub Copilot **agent mode**) runs local **stdio** MCP servers, so this uses the same
`GpibMcp.exe` directly.

## 1. Get the server
Download `__ZIP__` from the GitHub Release and unzip it to:

```
%LOCALAPPDATA%\Programs\GpibMcp
```

(so the server is at `__EXE__`). NI-VISA / NI-488.2 must be installed on the machine.

## 2a. One-click
Click an **Install in VS Code** link/badge, or open this URL:

```
__VSCODE_URL__
```

## 2b. Command line
```
__VSCODE_ADDCMD__
```

## 2c. Manual config
Add to your user `mcp.json` (Command Palette → **MCP: Open User Configuration**) or a workspace
`.vscode/mcp.json`:

```json
__CONFIG__
```

## 3. Use it
Open Copilot **Agent mode**, confirm the `gpib` server is started (Tools picker), then ask it to talk to
your instruments. Manage it via **MCP: List Servers**.
